Jadi hari ini (jumaat, 30/05/2025) sebelum 8 pagi saya dah dtg, saya orang pertama daftar, nombor giliran pertama. Lagi satu, kalau la memang sorang je doktor, 2 kerani depan tu buat apa? tak reti nak maklumkan ke? Maaf sbb saya terlalu marah, masa saya terbuang macam tu je. reviews.textTranslated:
Last Wednesday (28/05/2025, 8.57 am) I called SIMEE DENTAL CLINIC 05-5463415, a male officer answered and spoke to me (not sure of his name). I asked if I wanted to do teeth scaling, did I need to book an appointment or not. He said no need to book an appointment, you can just walk in Monday-Friday but you have to come early at 8 am or 2 pm.

So today (Friday, 30/05/2025) before 8 am I arrived, I was the first person to register, first queue number. When registering, the 2 counter clerks (also not sure of their names) made strange faces when I said I wanted scaling but they still gave me a queue number. If you are not sure, go confirm with the doctor first, don't waste people's time, if you can't do scaling, just say you can't, it's easy. I waited for an hour for my name to be called but no one came. There was a man who had been called first, I understand maybe he had already made an appointment. Less than 30 minutes is more than enough, but if it takes an hour, it's too much. The most painful thing is hearing the noise of the waiters and the food inside! I don't even care if I want to eat, but I have to work. Also, if there is only one doctor, what are the 2 front desk clerks doing? Don't you know how to inform me? Sorry for being so angry, my time is just wasted like that. The service is so bad, just throw away the customer charter if you can't improve the service. Isn't the upper management strict about this, because I'm sure I'm not the only one who has experienced this situation. I can't imagine if it happens to the elderly. Please, the relevant party takes this matter seriously. When I started to lose patience, I asked the counter staff how much longer I had to wait. Without saying sorry, I still had to wait, after 10 minutes I still wasn't called back. The 2 people at the counter didn't look like they had nothing to do, they were just waiting. Those 2 people don't deserve to be receptionists. BAD, BAD, BAD!

He not only has profound professional knowledge and rich clinical experience, but more importantly, he treats every patient with extreme care and patience, and never perfunctorily because of busyness or triviality.

What touched me most was that he never started from making money. In the process of diagnosis and treatment, he always insisted on basing himself on facts, analyzing the condition realistically, and never exaggerating or promoting unnecessary examinations or drugs. He always puts himself in the patient's shoes and recommends the most appropriate treatment plan, not the most expensive one. He often says: "The essence of medical care is to help people, not to profit from the patient's anxiety."

He is also very frank in communicating with patients. He does not conceal the condition or exaggerate the cause of the disease, but explains every detail in an easy-to-understand way, making people feel at ease and respected. He respects everyone's choice and is willing to spend time listening to the patient's doubts and ideas, making people feel the real trust and warmth between doctors and patients.
